simple_means.memory_skill: rend 给 + er 反复动作，连续动作；拟声动作 → 使成为；给予

tr: a substance similar to stucco but exclusively applied to masonry walls

example: The shot rendered her immobile

tr: melt (fat or lard) in order to separate out impurities
example: try the yak butter
render fat in a casserole

tr: restate (words) from one language into another language
example: I have to translate when my in-laws from Austria visit the U.S.
Can you interpret the speech of the visiting dignitaries?
She rendered the French poem into English
He translates for the U.N.
give homage
render thanks
render a verdict
deliver a judgment
render the brick walls in the den
The cow brings in 5 liters of milk
This year's crop yielded 1,000 bushels of corn
The estate renders some revenue for the family

tr: show in, or as in, a picture
example: This scene depicts country life
the face of the child is rendered with much tenderness in this painting

tr: give an interpretation or rendition of
example: The pianist rendered the Beethoven sonata beautifully

tr: to surrender someone or something to another
example: the guard delivered the criminal to the police
render up the prisoners
render the town to the enemy
fork over the money
render money
They had to render the estate

tr: give something useful or necessary to
example: We provided the room with an electrical heater

value.def: You can use render with an adjective that describes a particular state to say that someone or something is changed into that state. For example, if someone or something makes a thing harmless, you can say that they render it harmless.

example.ex: It contained so many errors as to render it worthless.
example.tran: 它错误太多,所以毫无用处。

example.ex: ...barrel-makers whose trade was rendered obsolete by the introduction of stainless steel wine vats.
example.tran: 不锈钢葡萄酒桶的出现使木制酒桶制造者没了生意

value.def: If you render someone help or service, you help them.

example.ex: He had a chance to render some service to his country...
example.tran: 他有了一个为国服务的机会。

example.ex: Any assistance you can render him will be appreciated...
example.tran: 无论给予他何种帮助，他都会非常感激。

example.ex: The money was in fact payment by the CIA for services rendered.
example.tran: 这些钱其实是中央情报局付给的工作报酬。

value.def: When a jury or authority renders a verdict, decision, or response, they announce it.

example.ex: The Board had been slow to render its verdict.
example.tran: 董事会迟迟未能作出决定。

value.tran: 宣布，作出(判决、决定或回应)

value.def: To render something in a particular language or in a particular way means to translate it into that language or in that way.

example.ex: ...'Zensho shimasu,' which the translator rendered literally as, 'I will do my best.'...
example.tran: “Zensho shimasu,”译者直译为“我会尽全力”。

example.ex: All the signs and announcements were rendered in English and Spanish.
example.tran: 所有的指示标志和公告都被译成了英语和西班牙语。

value.def: To render a wall means to cover it with a layer of plaster or cement, usually in order to protect it.

value.boxr_value: in AM, usually use 美国英语通常用 stucco
